Build the Create League / Tournament feature for the football app.

Goal:
A user must be able to create a league or tournament in under 30 seconds.

Required fields:
- competition_type (league | tournament)
- name
- age_group
- country
- city
- max_teams
- created_by_user_id

Optional fields:
- gender (boys | girls | mixed)
- competition_level (hobby | competitive | elite)
- organizer_type (club | association | private | school | company)
- organizer_id
- start_date
- end_date
- min_teams
- visibility (public | invite_only | private)
- registration_open
- registration_close

Create database table:
competitions

API endpoint:
POST /competitions

Example payload:

{
  "competition_type": "league",
  "name": "Helsinki Junior League U12",
  "age_group": "U12",
  "country": "Finland",
  "city": "Helsinki",
  "max_teams": 12,
  "created_by_user_id": "user_123"
}

Architecture:

Competition
 → Teams
 → Players

Competition does not own players directly.
Teams belong to competitions.
Players belong to teams.

After creation generate Competition Dashboard with:

- Teams
- Matches
- Standings
- Invitations
- Media
- Chat
